history.content: The thing about Math 1A is that the overwhelming majority of the students have taken this class in high school, and they have to repeat it for inflating their GPA or have not given AP tests (CoE bureaucracy). This can wreck ur curve if you have not taken this class before. From an objective sense, its syllabus is much shorter than most classes at Berkeley.

How much work is Math 1A for those who are familiar with most of the material and have taken other Math classes at Berkeley (1B and 53), as opposed to Physics 7A for those who are familiar with most of the concepts but have never taken a Physics class here?
